-- French Stocks Decline: ArcelorMittal, Saint-Gobain Retreat as Etam Gains
-- David Altaner
-- 2010-06-29T16:19:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-28/eurazeo-france-telecom-latecoere-sanofi-aventis-french-equity-preview.html

          
          
             France’s benchmark CAC 40 Index sank
143.46, or 4 percent, to 3,432.99 in Paris, the biggest decline
since May 14. The SBF 120 Index declined 3.8 percent.  
 The following are among the most active stocks traded in
France today.  
 ArcelorMittal  (MT NA) lost 6.3 percent to 22.79 euros. The
world’s biggest steelmaker fell after the Conference Board
revised its leading economic index for China to show the
smallest gain in five months in April.  
 Etam Developpement SA  (TAM FP) increased 7.3 percent to
34.98 euros. The women’s clothing designer and retailer said it
bought back 2.84 million shares at 35 euros apiece.  
 Cie. de Saint-Gobain SA  (SGO FP) declined 4.9 percent to
31.10 euros, the biggest drop since May 25. Europe’s largest
supplier of building materials agreed to sell its advanced
ceramics business to CoorsTek Inc. for $245 million.  
